    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-09-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in Central
                                America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Via El Paso, Tex.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 3, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Mizner reports the withdrawal of both armies from the frontiers and their
                    rapid disbandment, the success of the officious mediation of the diplomatic
                    corps, and the approval with which the country regards the course of that body.
                    He adds that the intention is to declare peace the coming week.</p>
            </div>
